  "bio_raw": "Dr. Ifat Al Baqee is serving as an Associate Professor in the department of Electrical and Electronic Engineering at University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh (ULAB). He obtained his Doctor of Philosophy (Ph.D.) in Computational Image Processing from Swinburne University of Technology, Australia at July 2016. He received his BSc. in Electrical and Electronics Engineering (EEE) from Military Institute of Science and Technology (MIST), Mirpur, Dhaka, February, 2009. From 2009 to 2012 he served as a Lecturer at the department of Electrical and Electronic Engineering, Stamford University Bangladesh. Since 2012 to 2016, he pursued his Doctoral degree and also had part time tutoring experience at Swinburne University of Technology, Australia in different capacities.\nDr. Baqee worked for several reputed private universities in Bangladesh as academic and researcher roles and he is more than 12 years of experiences in this sector. His research interests include image processing, audio processing and its application, wireless power transfer optimization, IoT based health system, and 3D modelling and automation and applications of AI in Health Monitoring and Image Processing. His research finding has been published in the leading journals and conferences in nationally and internationally.\nDr. Baqee has been thoroughly involved in OBE based teaching learning curriculum and accreditation process. He worked in undergraduate curriculum development committee for BSc in EEE program of Southeast University Bangladesh from Bangladesh Accreditation Council on 2021-22. He acquired administrative experiences from the role of Head of the EEE department at University of Information, Technology and Sciences during 2022-24. He also served as Additional Director, IQAC of Canadian University of Bangladesh as well as Head of the department of EEE at Canadian University of Bangladesh.\nHe is also currently involved in the editorial committee of several reputed international journals search as IACSIT, AJEIT and performed responsibilities of Co-Chair and Chair of IEEE conference sessions such as ICREST and ICCIT.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Signal Processing, Image Optimization, IoT, Electronic Health Monitoring, AI in Healthcare and Smart Wearables."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nPhD\n, Swinburne University of Technology, Australia\nBSc\nin EECE, MIST"
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Journal Articles\nIfat Al Baqee\n,\n‘A convex optimization approach to parallel magnetic resonance imaging reconstruction’\n, published in International Journal of Biomedical Engineering and Technology, 41(2), pp. 126-144.\nhttps://doi.org/10.1504/IJBET.2023.129192\nIfat-Al Baqee\n,\n‘A Novel Approach of Obtaining Optimal Solution for E-SPIRIT’\n, published in Southeast University Journal of Electrical and Electronic Engineering (SEUJEEE), 2(1), pp. 21-28.\nIfat-Al Baqee\n,\n‘A Convex Optimization based Approach to Reduce External Noise from pMRI Images’\n, published in Southeast University Journal of Electrical and Electronic Engineering (SEUJEEE), 1(2), pp. 13-18.\nIfat-Al Baqee\n,\n‘A Relative Comparison between Noise Performances of Different pMRI Algorithms’\n, published in Southeast University Journal of Electrical and Electronic Engineering (SEUJEEE), 1(1), pp. 1-6.\nIfat-Al-Baqee\n, Mehedi Hasan Sumon, Kamol Kanto Das, Mohammad Umar Saad, Shakil Seeraji,\n‘A Neural Network-Based Face Recognition Method by Illumination Normalization & Edge Detection’\n, published in International Journal of Applied Engineering Research (IJAER), 6(17), pp. 2069-2077.\nhttps://www.scopus.com/sourceid/21100217234",
    "Conference Proceedings\nMuhammad Raisuddin Ahmed, Mohammed A Aseeri, Thirein MYO, M Shamim Kaiser,\nIfat Al Baqee\n, Mohammad Hamiruce Marhaban,\n‘Efficient Hybrid Anomaly Detection in Environmental Data’\n, published in 6th International Conference on Trends in Computational and Cognitive Engineering (TCCE 2024), ID: 2024060015, India, 2025.\nMohd. Hamim, Sumit Paul, Syed Iqramul Hoque, Md. Nafiur Rahman,\nIfat-Al Baqee\n,\n‘IoT Based Remote Health Monitoring System for Patients and Elderly People’\n, published in 2019 International Conference on Robotics, Electrical and Signal Processing Techniques (ICREST) (IEEE Xplore), Bangladesh, 2019.\nCishen Zhang and\nIfat-Al-Baqee\n,\n‘Parallel magnetic resonance imaging reconstruction by convex optimization’\n, published in 2013 Third International Conference on Innovative Computing Technology (INTECH), UK, 2013.\nJiaxi He, Cishen Zhang and\nIfat-Al-Baqee\n,\n‘Image Dehazing Using Regularized Optimization’\n, published in Part I Proceedings of 10th International Symposium, ISVC 2014, Las Vegas, NV, USA, 2014.\nIfat-Al-Baqee\n, Cishen Zhang and Xin GAO,\n‘Optimal parallel MRI reconstruction over a convex solution space’\n, published in 2015 IEEE International Conference on Signal Processing, Communications and Computing (ICSPCC), China, 2015.\nJiaxi He, Cishen Zhang,\nIfat-Al-Baqee\nand Xin Gao,\n‘A regularized optimization approach to fast image dehazing’\n, published in 2015 IEEE International Conference on Signal Processing, Communications and Computing (ICSPCC), China, 2015.\nCishen Zhang,\nIfat-Al-Baqee\nand Jingxin Zhang,\n‘Parallel MRI Reconstruction by Direct Convex Optimization’\n, Presented in ISMRM 23rd Annual Meeting and Exhibition, Ontario, Canada, 2015.\nKai Zhu, Cishen Zhang, Jingxin Zhang,\nIfat-Al Baqee\n, Sulaiman A. Al Hasani,\n‘Convex Optimization for 3D Parallel MRI Reconstruction’\n, published in ICSPS 2016 Proceedings of the 8th International Conference on Signal Processing Systems, Auckland, New Zealand, 2016.",
